        <h2>Criminal Legal System Reform & Drug Policy: Rewriting the Rules</h2>
        <p>Our <strong>Criminal Legal System Reform</strong> program operates a full-service legislative advocacy shop at the Arizona Capitol. During the 2025 session, we co-sponsored SB 1507 establishing independent oversight. We also championed bills ending mandatory minimums for drug possession, creating "second look" sentencing review for juveniles sentenced as adults, limiting probation terms, expanding compassionate release for elderly incarcerated people, and requiring prosecutors to disclose racial impact data on plea deals.</p>
        <p>Simultaneously, our <strong>Drug Policy & Overdose Prevention</strong> program addresses Arizona's fatal overdose epidemic. We distribute naloxone to returning citizens and families, train incarcerated people in overdose response for post-release preparedness, and lobby for harm reduction policies. Our peer-led "Harm Reduction in the Hood" program operates in Maryvale and South Tucson, offering wound care, fentanyl test strips, and connections to treatment without law enforcement involvement. Both programs share a core belief: punishment worsens substance use; community support saves lives.</p>
